                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200628-122-off671 t18200628-122-crimeloc673"></join>. The prisoner, I am sorry to say, is my son. On the 24th of January, at nine o'clock in the morning, the cart was safe; and about four o'clock in the morning I missed it. The officer produced it to me on the Monday following with the harness. I never gave my son leave to take it - he did not live with me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not give it to me - A. Never.</p>
